as how the causes and consequences of state failure have been addressed, and presents analyses to deal with these problems. Any analysis of state failure can be seen as an exercise in policy evaluation; this book undertakes the theoretical, conceptual, and analytic work that must be done before we can evaluate-or have much confidence in-both current and proposed policy prescriptions to prevent or manage state collapse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aFailed states. 4acivil war. 4ademocracy. 4adiffusion. 4aeconomic development. 4ainterstate war. 4apolitical instability. 4apost-World War II system. 4astate collapse. 4astate failure. 4aweak/fragile states. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh1 aStarr, Harvey, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479691040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804796910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804796910.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles